<br>
w/o having 50k to blow on 2 lammies and a 2her that does as much damage as 2 lammies; I still stand by my perceptions , albiet level 34 perceptions , that it's the damage and not the sheer # of hits that is the true taunt factor. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujuujuu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Juujuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 856<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/29/01 1:53:19 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://216.242.60.166/chicktourney_com/larges/415.jpg width=110 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: \</span><hr size=1> the number of time you hit a mob has some part in how much you taunt.  It's why rangers can out taunt a warrior who does more damage with slower 1h weapons.  Most ranger 1h weapons are very fast.   <p>=============================
<br>Juujuu Bigmojo
<br>58 Halfling Shaman
<br><img src=http://www.tbp.mb.ca/~stimpy/everquest/JuujuuHalflingSentry.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubeatrixmaledicta.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beatrix Maledicta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/30/01 1:48:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior 2HS Question</span><hr size=1> My guess is we go wrong if we neglect looking at the specific weapons in this case. Sunderfury is a pretty crazy weapon with a 25/36 ratio. At 52 you get a +10 dmg bonus too, which indirectly affects the ratio of the weapon if wielded in the main hand. Wurmslayer is 25/40 - a worse ratio. Now since you are dual wielding it with a Kunzar the 1H combo should come out on top as far as dmg output goes. And dmg output is a great taunt - every warrior is sadly aware of that. <br>
<br>
However, the added value of the off-hand weapon isn't always as high as one might think. I know that at lvl 50 there is only a 41.67% chance for an offhand swing. I don't know what it would be at 52 (post 50 cap) with a maxed dual wield. I doubt it is much higher than say 43% though. The dmg/dly of the Kunzar is quite a bit worse than the WS too and you don't get the benefit of a dmg bonus in the off-hand.<br>
<br>
My personal guess is that if it was possible to switch hands with the WS/Kunzar combo you would notice a difference in &quot;tauntability&quot;. But this shouldn't be confused with &quot;be able to taunt&quot;, where you have to take other group members and their equipment/spells/actions into account. Often either you manage to keep the mob taunted or you don't, but it's when the mob flickers between you and the other meleers that you may notice a difference with various weapons.<br>
<br>
Perhaps warriors have been a little too hesitant to use 2HS for taunting purposes. It seems there is also a certain coolness factor involved with getting expensive or hard-to-acquire low dly 1HS weapons rather than 2H. Still, I think there is some truth in the belief that 2H on average is a worse taunt and only so because of lower dmg output, missed blows accounted for. What &quot;worse&quot; means depends, I suppose.<br>
 <p><b>Beatrix Maledicta</b><br>
Barbie warrioress who can count to 52<br><br>
<img src="http://medlem.tripodnet.nu/beatrix_maledicta/Beatrix3.jpg" border="0"><br>




</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujarrelkildum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarrel Kildum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 189<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/7/01 10:56:55 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://jarrelkildum.homestead.com/files/c_warrior.gif width=80 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior 2HS Question</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the feedback on this.  I'm still switching my weapons to test em out but the group makeup definately has to do with your &quot;tauntability&quot;.  <br>
<br>
In certain situations, the 1Hder's work good, in others the 2Hder does the trick.  What I've been doing lately is switching out weapons until I consume as much of the mobs attention as I can, which is what it's all about anyways if your a warrior.  And in some cases it's 1HS, in other's it 2HS or 2HB (need to work on my 1HB skill).<br>
<br>
I'm not no mathmatician (hell I can't even spell it lol) but I guess you just gotta get a feel for the environment your in to see what works best <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Thanks again...<br>
<br>
Jarrel <p><img src="http://eq.geauxonline.com/images/jklogo.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uredspinebladeslinge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Redspine Bladeslinge</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 939<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/7/01 3:52:13 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.yellowspine.com/images/jestur01.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior 2HS Question</span><hr size=1> If another melee is in group using 2 1hs weapons, I can have difficulty taunting with a 2hs.  I can taunt the mob, but might have problems keeping it off the other melee.  It's very seldom though that I have taunting issues in any group.  When I do I switch out to my 2hs.  Also, although not extraordinary stats, a Scopolisk Impaler helps with taunting.  Think this weapon has a 120-140dmg dot.  In my off hand I get at least 2 procs a fight.  I also like it for fun when just my wife and I are fighting alone. <p><img border="1" src="http://www.yellowspine.com/images/char1.bmp" width="360" height="94"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessage?topicID=450.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessage?topicID=445.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.threadControl?topicID=478.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http